						prototype engineering internship at Kinoma  


				%div.section
					.title.grid-33 user group

					.description.prefix-33 Kinoma Create users, makers 


				%div.section
					.title.grid-33 goal

					.description.prefix-33 I wanted to show customers that the appearance of the Kinoma Create is customizable, provide a basic blueprint for laser cutting an enclosure and outline a way to safely transplant the electronics into a new enclosure.

				%div.section
					.title.grid-33 notes

					.description.prefix-33 During my process, I damaged several ribbon cables, causing the touch screens on units to malfunction. I consulted with electronics experts to diagnose the issues and kept track of best practices to protect the electronics during the assembly. 
					


				%div.section
					.title.grid-33 testing

					.description.prefix-33 After arriving at a case + instructions, I observed 3 members of the team build the case to make sure that safe results were reproduced and made revisions to meet their confusions. 

				%div.section
					.title.grid-33 outcome

					.description.prefix-33 I ended up with a 3-piece wooden case, assembled with flat head screws, nuts and rubber grommets. 
